{"article_id":"pdoDHXGga3RIEJGP","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Judge Brett Kavanaugh on Friday moved a step closer to being seated on the Supreme Court ,","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"as four days of chaotic and tumultuous hearings wrapped","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"with Kavanaugh largely having swatted away Democratic attempts","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"to derail his nomination .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"Democrats spent the week trying to catch Kavanaugh in a lie","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"and employ old emails","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"to cast him as a radical conservative .","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"But Republicans say","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"they believe","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"Democrats failed to land a fatal blow .","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell , R-Ky. , said","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"he had no doubts \" whatsoever \"","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"that Kavanaugh would ultimately be confirmed .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"\" I think","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"any doubts","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"anybody might have","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"had been dispelled by his virtuoso performance before the Judiciary Committee , \"","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"McConnell told radio host Hugh Hewitt .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"`` I mean ,","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"it ' s stunning .","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"He ' s just a stellar nomination in every respect . \"","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"After grilling Kavanaugh for two days ,","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"senators on Friday heard from outside witnesses","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"both supporting and opposing the nominee ,","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"marking the end of the hearing process .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"Among those","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"invited by the Democrats on the committee","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"was John Dean , the former Nixon White House counsel","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"who turned against the administration during Watergate .","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"Dean , a Trump critic , predicted","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"that with Kavanaugh on the high court , it will become `` a weak check , at best , on presidential power . ''","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"He called the scenario `` deeply troubling , ''","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"adding","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"that there is `` much to fear from an unchecked president","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"who is inclined to abuse his powers . ''","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"Meanwhile , members of an American Bar Association committee gave Kavanaugh their highest rating of `` well qualified ''","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"based on his integrity , competence and judicial temperament .","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"John Tarpley , the lead evaluator in the review , told the committee Friday","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"it was clear","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"based on interviews with peers","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"that Kavanaugh learned integrity at an early age .","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"He said","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"Kavanaugh received high praise for his knowledge of the law and for his judicial temperament ,","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"with reviewers saying","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"he was affable","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"and kept an open mind .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"The Judiciary Committee , in the coming days and weeks , is expected to vote on Kavanaugh ' s confirmation","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"before the nomination heads to the full Senate for a final vote .","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"\" We look forward to the Judiciary Committee completing its review","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"and advancing his nomination , \"","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"said White House Spokesman Raj Shah .","depth":5},{"id":51,"text":"Democrats were always going to have a tough time","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"defeating Kavanaugh .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"But","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"with Republicans enjoying only a 51-49 majority ,","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"a couple defections would be enough","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"to stall his confirmation .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"But Republicans have held together","depth":6},{"id":58,"text":"and accused Democrats","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"-- under pressure from their base , and some flirting with a presidential bid --","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"of turning the hearings into a `` circus .","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"'' \" This hearing","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"-- really quite frankly --","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"was sad","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"and became a joke , \"","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"Sen. Lindsey Graham , R-S.C. , said Friday on \" Fox & Friends . \"","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"\" Those hearings were a circus , \"","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"Sen. Ben Sasse , R-Neb. , said on \" Fox News @ Night. \"","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"\" There was so much nonsense , consistent dishonesty , in the way","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"people would ask their questions . \"","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"Among the most bizarre turn of events at Kavanaugh ' s hearing was when Democratic Sen. Cory Booker on Thursday vowed to publicly release past emails of Kavanaugh ' s","depth":5},{"id":71,"text":"that were marked confidential in an act of \" civil disobedience . \"","depth":5},{"id":72,"text":"BRETT KAVANAUGH VOWS TO 'KEEP AN OPEN MIND IN EVERY CASE '","depth":4},{"id":73,"text":"Booker , a possible 2020 presidential candidate , said","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"he was prepared to face punishment","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"for doing so .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"he was doing so draw attention to Republicans ' \" sham process . \"","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"\" This is about the closest","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"I 'll probably ever have in my life to an , ' I am Spartacus ' moment , \"","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"Booker said Thursday .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"But Booker didn ' t actually break the rules with that release .","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"The Republicans on the Judiciary Committee said","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"they worked with the George W. Bush library and the Justice Department overnight","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"to clear the emails .","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"The restrictions were waived early Thursday morning .","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"\" All of this drama this morning apparently was for nothing","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"and it ' s unfortunate , \"","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"Sen. John Cornyn , R-Texas , told reporters Thursday .","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"Still , Booker ,","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"insisting","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"he was violating Senate rules ,","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"continued to post more emails via Twitter afternoon","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"that","depth":14},{"id":94,"text":"he said","depth":14},{"id":95,"text":"were designated `` confidential . ''","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"\" Senate Republicans are doing everything","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"they can","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"to distract from their sham process","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"to rush through a Supreme Court justice","depth":14},{"id":100,"text":"who will overturn Roe v. Wade ,","depth":15},{"id":101,"text":"demolish the Affordable Care Act ,","depth":16},{"id":102,"text":"and protect President Trump from being investigated , \"","depth":16},{"id":103,"text":"Booker said .","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"One email release","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"that caused a stir","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"pertained to the Roe v. Wade decision","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"ensuring the right to an abortion","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"-- and showed Kavanaugh","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"discussing","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"whether the issue was settled law .","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"\" I am not sure","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"that all legal scholars refer to Roe as the settled law of the land at the Supreme court level","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"since Court can always overrule its precedent ,","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"and three current Justices on the Court would do so , \"","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"Kavanaugh said in a 2003 email .","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"Democrats used the email","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"to suggest","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"he could vote to overturn abortion rights .","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"But","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"when asked by Sen. Dianne Feinstein , D.-Calif. , the ranking member of the Senate Judiciary Committee , to clarify his thoughts ,","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"Kavanaugh said","depth":14},{"id":122,"text":"he was referring in the email to \" what legal scholars \" might say .","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"\" I think","depth":15},{"id":124,"text":"my comment in the email was","depth":16},{"id":125,"text":"that might be overstating the position of legal scholars","depth":16},{"id":126,"text":"and so it wasn ' t a technically accurate description in the letter of what legal scholars thought , \"","depth":14},{"id":127,"text":"Kavanaugh said ,","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"adding ,","depth":15},{"id":129,"text":"\" The broader point was simply that","depth":15},{"id":130,"text":"I think","depth":16},{"id":131,"text":"it was overstating something about legal scholars ,","depth":16},{"id":132,"text":"and I ' m always concerned with accuracy ,","depth":15},{"id":133,"text":"and I thought","depth":14},{"id":134,"text":"that was not quite [ an ] accurate description of all legal scholars","depth":15},{"id":135,"text":"because it referred to all . \"","depth":15},{"id":136,"text":"In an another combative moment , Sen. Kamala Harris , D-Calif. , another possible Democratic presidential candidate , on Wednesday asked Kavanaugh","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"whether he ever had discussed Special Counsel Robert Mueller or his Russia probe with anyone at Kasowitz Benson Torres , the law firm","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"founded by Marc Kasowitz , a former personal attorney to President Trump .","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"\" I don ' t recall any conversations of that kind with anyone at that law firm...","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"I haven ' t had any inappropriate conversations about that investigation with anyone , \"","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"Kavanaugh said Thursday ,","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"when given the chance","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"to elaborate on Harris ' question from a day earlier .","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"He added ,","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"\" I ' ve never given anyone any hints , forecasts , previews , winks , nothing about my view as a judge or how I would rule as a judge on that or anything","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"related to that . \"","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"Graham , the South Carolina Republican , said","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"that line of questioning from Harris \" bothered me the most . \"","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"\" That line of questioning","depth":11},{"id":150,"text":"I think","depth":11},{"id":151,"text":"is inappropriate , \"","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":153,"text":"\" If you do n't like him","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"vote no .","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"But do n't suggest","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"this man is anything other than honest . \"","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"For the most part , the hearings have focused on Kavanaugh ' s writings and , in particular , key opinions","depth":5},{"id":158,"text":"he authored","depth":6},{"id":159,"text":"while serving on the nation ' s most prestigious appellate court .","depth":6},{"id":160,"text":"Kavanaugh served for more than a decade on the D.C . Circuit Court of Appeals and , before that , for five years as a lawyer in the White House Counsel ' s office in the George W. Bush administration .","depth":5},{"id":161,"text":"He also worked for independent counsel Ken Starr for three years during the probe","depth":6},{"id":162,"text":"that led to the impeachment of former President Bill Clinton .","depth":6},{"id":163,"text":"Kavanaugh ' s elevation from the D.C . Circuit Court of Appeals to the Supreme Court would mark a generational rightward shift on the Supreme Court ,","depth":4},{"id":164,"text":"raising the stakes beyond those of last year ' s nomination of Neil Gorsuch .","depth":4},{"id":165,"text":"Party leaders have said","depth":3},{"id":166,"text":"they hope to have Kavanaugh confirmed by a floor vote by early October ,","depth":4},{"id":167,"text":"when the next Supreme Court term begins .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":335,"left":324,"right":334,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":324,"left":218,"right":323,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":218,"left":213,"right":217,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":213,"left":188,"right":212,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":188,"left":171,"right":187,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":171,"left":0,"right":170,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":170,"left":1,"right":169,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":169,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":187,"left":176,"right":186,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":173,"right":175,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":173,"left":4,"right":172,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":172,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":7,"right":174,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":174,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":186,"left":178,"right":185,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":10,"right":177,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":177,